## DM vs Group Detection

Telegram convention: positive `chatId` = private/DM, negative `chatId` = group/supergroup/channel. Use `chatId > 0` to detect DMs. The `extractChatId` function in `inbound.ts` already returns a number, so this check is straightforward.

## grammY Compatibility

The `sendMessageDraft` method may not be available in all grammY versions. The implementation uses a `try/catch` around the call and silently falls back to buffer-and-flush if it fails. No startup check is needed since the error is caught per-call.

